Knutson began performing improv comedy in 2006, and stand-up in 2009.
He won Acme Comedy Company's "Funniest Person in the Twin Cities" contest in 2010.
"Knutson formed Valley Meadows in 2008 with Zach Coulter.
The duo also starred in an online video series, Valley Meadows, in 2014, which Knutson wrote.

The webseries was nominated for four awards at the 2015 Los Angeles Web Series Festival: Outstanding Comedy Series, Outstanding Writing, Outstanding Lead Actor (for Knutson), and Outstanding Guest Actor (for Dan Susmilch).
In 2012, laughspin.com nominated Valley Meadows for its Readers Choice Award for Best Musical Comedy Act.
Knutson and his wife had a son in 2014, and fatherhood quickly become a main topic of his comedy.
Another video series, Baby Cop, followed in 2014–15.
His solo stand-up album Rewound was recorded at Sisyphus Brewing in Minneapolis in 2015 and released in 2021.
